<br>
I will also try to keep these as general as possible, without mention of level specific spells.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> --Shadow Knight--</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Preparation-</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Buff</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Before hand. Buff yourself with every buff you have. Guard series, Spirit Armor series, Symbol series, and any endures/resists you have at your disposal (Magic and Poison are the two most important). Also be sure and med back to full before starting.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Spells</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Barring odd instances, mem the following spells: 2 heals, 1 nuke, 1 root, 2 stuns, 1-2 Divines. If you are duelling before level 29, you will have only one Divine at your disposal. In it's place, mem Flash of Light.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Battle-</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Harm Touch (HT)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Most SKs love opening up the duel with a well placed HT. You can nullify this by simply using Divine Aura/Divine Barrier right before callenging/accepting a duel. After the HT has been spent while you were invulnerable, left click on the buff icon to cancel it, so you can start casting.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Root Park the Shadow Knight</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Root the Shadow Knight first. Then back away from him to draw his pet (assuming he summoned one). When root breaks, reapply ASAP. Only reapply root when it is broken, otherwise you may waste valuable mana.<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Root Park the pet</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Root the pet second. The pet dies when the SK does, so you need not worry about the pet. If the SK cons even or less to you, then the pet is green, and will not hit you enough or do enough damage to you to worry about. When root breaks, reapply ASAP. Only reapply root when it is broken, otherwise you may waste valuable mana.<br>
<br>
4) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Meditate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> As often as necessary, I would say no later than when nearing 20m. Get out of the Shadow Knight's spell casting range, sit, and med. You'll need all the mana you can get/keep/regen. If root breaks while medding, reapply, back away.. and continue medding. Your mana will regen faster than his health, by a long shot, so don't feel as if you're losing ground.<br>
<br>
5) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Stuns</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Use your memmed stun(s) in between casts of your nuke/root. If you time your stuns right, the SK will never get a spell off. Always be mindful of the partical effects. Most, if not all, SK spells have a much longer casting time than any Stun at the Clerics disposal.<br>
<br>
6) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Nukes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> After the SK and pet are effectively rooted, and you are at a sufficienct amount of mana, jump inside spell casting range, and nuke. Watch the SK and cast stuns as necessary. When you have only about 30% mana left, leave the spell range, and sit and med. Repeat as necessary, bein watchful of root breaks. <p><center>
